      <lg xml:id="TolE0438">
<l>mutalī reṇṇiṉoṟṟu rakara māku</l>
<l>mukaram varuta lāvayi ṉāṉa</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>The consonant of the first two numbers changes into <foreign xml:lang="ta">ṟ</foreign> ; and the</l>
<l>sound <foreign xml:lang="ta">u</foreign> joins [it] at that place.<note place="foot">I.e. the <foreign xml:lang="ta">ṉ</foreign> and <foreign xml:lang="ta">ṇ</foreign>
          of <foreign xml:lang="ta">oṉṟu</foreign> and <foreign xml:lang="ta">iraṇṯu</foreign> are
          respectively replaced by <foreign xml:lang="ta">r</foreign> and followed by <foreign xml:lang="ta">u,</foreign> eg. <foreign xml:lang="ta">oṉṟu + pattu &gt; oṉ + pahtu
          &gt; orupahtu.</foreign></note></l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
